The paper discusses a new notion of stability for computations that ensures generalization in the face of adaptivity. This concept is relevant to machine learning and data privacy, which are both covered by the cs.LG and cs.CR categories. The paper also involves quantifying the effect of observing a computation's outputs, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between this stability notion and differentially private algorithms, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
